curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/3211' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM8042", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM8042 is a dual, high precision operational  amplifier which can operate from 1.4V to 5.5V single  supply, while consuming only 670nA/amplifier quiescent  current. It provides rail-to-rail input and output operation.  Therefore, the SGM8042 is suitable for use in portable  instrumentation and battery-powered systems.  The SGM8042 is unity-gain stable, and features a  14.5kHz gain-bandwidth product. It is designed to  provide optimal performance in low frequency systems,  when monitoring battery current and conditioning sensor  signal.  The SGM8042 is available in Green SOIC-8 and MSOP-8  packages. It is specified over the extended -40℃ to +85℃  temperature range.  "}'
